	<header>
		<h1><a href="http://foodsense.is/blog/recipe-laurens-general-tsaos-tofu">Recipe: Lauren&#8217;s General Tsao&#8217;s Tofu</a></h1>
			</header>
		
	<div class="group">
		<img src="http://foodsense.is/uploads/post-images/General_Tsaos_Tofu.jpg" class="post-image border" alt="image" />		<p><a href="http://foodsense.is/blog/lauren-monologue">Yesterday, Lauren told us how she went veg in junior high, how she approaches cooking, and how she handles Thanksgiving with her non-veg extended family.</a></p>

<p>On cooking at home for herself and her non-vegetarian husband, she said: </p>

<blockquote><p>I try to make things that he likes that are vegetarian. He likes to order General Tsao’s chicken at Chinese restaurants, and so over the years, I’ve perfected my General Tsao’s tofu recipe, which he loves.</p>

<p>It’s a good challenge for me to find things I can cook for us both, so that he doesn’t feel like he’s missing out. I personally...</p></blockquote>
		<p><a href="http://foodsense.is/blog/recipe-laurens-general-tsaos-tofu">Continue reading &raquo;</a></p>	</div>
	
